(Photo by Jemal Countess/Getty Images for the 2015 ... more James Franco playing Rachel on 'Friends' is bizarre and mesmerizing 1  /  1 Back to Gallery James Franco, human parody of himself, is confounding audiences once again with a new "spoof" clip featuring him playing the role of Rachel (and also Joey) on "Friends" for an AOL original series called "Making a Scene."
In the clip, the classic fake TV gang is sitting at fake Central Perk singing "Smelly Cat" (typical) when fake Ross rushes in to ready the group for fake Marcel the monkey's intervention.
The episode is not the first of its kind. Actually, Franco has already parodied several other shows, including "Freaks and Geeks" (a show in which he starred), "Breaking Bad," "Sex & the City," and more.
View the NSFW (language) video clip here , and the full episode here .
